{"id":668902808,"lang":"swift","time":"3 months, 1 week","timestamp":1648465262,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"20 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/668902808/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"14.8 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    func romanToInt(_ s: String) -> Int {\n        let hashMap : [Character : Int] = [\n            \"I\" : 1,\n            \"V\" : 5,\n            \"X\" : 10,\n            \"L\" : 50,\n            \"C\" : 100,\n            \"D\" : 500,\n            \"M\" : 1000,\n        ]\n        \n        var outputSum = 0\n        \n        var lastChar: Character? = nil\n        for currentChar in s.reversed() {\n            if let lastChar = lastChar {\n                if currentChar == \"I\" && (lastChar == \"V\" || lastChar == \"X\" ) { outputSum -= 1 }\n                else if currentChar == \"X\" && (lastChar == \"L\" || lastChar == \"C\" ) { outputSum -= 10 }\n                else if currentChar == \"C\" && (lastChar == \"D\" || lastChar == \"M\" ) { outputSum -= 100 }\n                else { outputSum += hashMap[currentChar]! }\n            } else {\n                outputSum += hashMap[currentChar]!\n            }\n            \n            lastChar = currentChar\n        }\n        \n        return outputSum\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer"}
